main event: On March 28, 1960, three unidentified objects were observed moving at high speeds over Duluth, Minnesota, detected by radar.
interesting points: The objects were seen moving at approximately three times the speed of satellites., One object appeared bright yellowish while the other two appeared dull reddish., The observation lasted for approximately 5 to 10 minutes., There is documentation connecting the sighting to NASA communications and Project Blue Book., The incident was reported by Mrs. James Norman, which led to further investigations.
witness description: Mrs. James Norman reported the sighting.
